@startuml
title Diagrama de Componentes - Sistema Integrado BBVA Perú Simulado

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

skinparam component {
  BackgroundColor #F4F6F8
  BorderColor #072146
  FontColor #072146
}

skinparam database {
  BackgroundColor #EAF4FF
  BorderColor #0726B4
  FontColor #072146
}

actor "Cliente BBVA" as Cliente
actor "Personal del Banco" as Personal

package "Homebanking BBVA" {
  component "Frontend Homebanking\nReact + Vite\nPuerto 5173" as HBFront
  component "Backend Homebanking\nFastAPI\nPuerto 8000" as HBBack
}

package "Core Bancario BBVA" {
  component "Frontend Core\nReact + Vite\nPuerto 5174" as CoreFront
  component "Backend Core\nFastAPI\nPuerto 8001" as CoreBack
}

database "PostgreSQL\nbd_core_financiero" as DB {
  component "app_usuarios" as TUsuarios
  component "cuentas" as TCuentas
  component "transacciones" as TTransacciones
  component "solicitudes_prestamo" as TSolicitudes
  component "pagos" as TPagos
  component "dpersonal / roles core" as TRoles
}

component "Power BI\nDashboard Financiero" as PowerBI

Cliente --> HBFront : usa
HBFront --> HBBack : API REST
HBBack --> DB : consulta / registra

Personal --> CoreFront : usa
CoreFront --> CoreBack : API REST
CoreBack --> DB : consulta / actualiza

DB --> PowerBI : indicadores financieros

DB --> TUsuarios
DB --> TCuentas
DB --> TTransacciones
DB --> TSolicitudes
DB --> TPagos
DB --> TRoles

note bottom of DB
Ambos sistemas comparten la misma base de datos.
Esto permite el flujo end-to-end:
Homebanking solicita crédito -> Core aprueba/desembolsa -> Homebanking refleja saldo.
end note

@enduml